  <modalFeedback identifier="CORRECT_FEEDBACK" outcomeIdentifier="GENERAL_FEEDBACK" showHide="show">
    <p>
      <b>Option A (Factor VIIa) is correct.</b>
      Factor VII is activated to Factor VIIa when bound to tissue factor. Factor VIIa has a role in the activation of Factor X, as does the Factor VIIIa/Factor IXa complex, minor at first but then accelerated through further activation of Factor VII by small amounts of Factor Xa. This is the end of the extrinsic pathway where it joins with the intrinsic pathway.
    </p>
  </modalFeedback>
